>A Roo'd Awakening
>https://pastebin.com/muScjRyj
Read through Ch 4 (all the greentext format). Planning to finish in the next day or so.

One thing that started to irritate is the overuse of Aussie slang. In particular, you can probably delete a full half the times she says "mate." I worked & lived in an Aussie expat community for nearly half a decade. Very rarely ever heard any of them use the word 'Mate.' And, when they do, it's not quite so casual. It's most often reserved for other Aussies and (usually Aussie) friends who truly are mates.

That stood out enough to make mention. We get it that she's a Roo'd Gal from Down Under. That point can stand easily enough with a bit more subtle hand. Not saying don't do any of the lingo & bantz, just back off a bit. I'll stop by after finishing, but most comments I'd make regarding style at this point are not relevant for the rough state the greentext portion is in.

Overall, NOICE / 10
